OL,3,CArriva bus workers announce strike
OL,4,Caction in Spring
OL,6,FThe union's regional officer Dave
OL,7,FTelford said: "This strike
OL,8,Fdemonstrates the strength of ill-
OL,9,Ffeeling at Arriva over the poor pay
OL,10,Foffer they've offered our members when
OL,11,Fenergy bills and mortgages have gone
OL,12,Fthrough the roof. Unite will be
OL,13,Fbacking them 100%."
OL,15,FA spokesperson for Arriva North East
OL,16,Fsaid: "Arriva will continue to work
OL,17,Fwith Unite and try our best to find
OL,18,Fthe most appropriate resolution."
